8.  OUTPUT PRODUCTS AND AVAILABILITY

8.1  Tape Products.   None.

8.2  Film Products.   None.

8.3  Other Products.

8.3.1.  SMM/ACRIM Daily Averages,  Level II.

      Medium/Specifications:  The SMM/ACRIM Daily Averages are available on
      JPL's Hewlett-Packard system disk (running UNIX) from the producer.

      Format/Content:  The daily averages of solar irradiance and the
      standard error calculations are contained in one ASCII file with the
      corresponding mission day.

      Data Quantity/Rate:  Approximately 79 kilo-bytes.  There is one solar
      irradiance value and standard error calculation per day.

      Status:  The data are available through July 14, 1989.

      Plans/Schedule:  The release of additional data through the end of
      the mission is uncertain.  Orbit degradation during the last months
      of operation may have affected the solar flux values.

8.3.2  SMM/ACRIM Daily Averages,  Level II

      Medium/Specifications:  The data are also available on-line through
      NASA's Climate Data System.  Data are stored in a data structure
      called the Common Data Format (CDF) and are available without NCDS
      staff assistance.

      Format/Content:  The data are available in Common Data Format (CDF).
      This format allows all attributes describing the data to be stored
      internally in the data file itself.  The data set name used to access
      the data in NCDS is "SMM-ACRIM".  The data consist of daily averaged
      total solar irradiance and standard error calculations with the
      corresponding mission day and date.

      Data Quantity/Rate:  Approximately 108 kilo-bytes.  There is one
      solar irradiance value and standard error calculation per day.

      Status:  These data are currently available through NCDS from
      February 1980 through July 14, 1989.  Official release of additional
      data through the end of the data set are uncertain due to orbit
      degradation of the satellite.

      Plans/Schedule:  NCDS archives all available data and will update the
      CDF data file if and when new data are received.


