12.  RELATED DATA SETS

Solar irradiance values are available from the Hickey-Frieden (HF)
radiometer on the Nimbus-7 Earth Radiation Budget (ERB) experiment since
December 1978.  For additional information see the detailed data set
description for the N7-ERB data set in NCDS.  Solar irradiance values from
December 1978 to the present are also available from the Solar Backscatter
Ultraviolet sensor on Nimbus-7 as part of the Continuous Scan Solar Flux
Tape (SUNC).


13.  SUMMARY/SAMPLE

A sample plot showing solar irradiance values over the entire data set
range is available through the Data Applications Subsystem of NCDS. Specify
"SMM-ACRIM" as input to the "Display Sample of Data Set" option in the NCDS
graphics subsystem.

14.  NOTES

The next solar monitoring experiment, ACRIM II, is aboard the Upper
Atmosphere Research Satellite (UARS), which was launched in September,
1991.


